                            <comment id="12980320" author="dagw" created="Tue, 11 Jan 2011 20:42:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch which lets checkCancellationFlag throw SQLState.CONN_INTERRUPT (the thread&apos;s interrupt flag is also set).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The exception was generated at the time the interrupt was seen so the stack trace would show exactly when this was picked up. Possibly we should wrap it in another to show that we are throwing in checkCancellationFlag.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
